We have created a hidden Add modal trigger inside the Laravel project that does not appear anywhere on the screen. Instead of clicking a button, the modal opens automatically when the user types a secret keyword: "addnow" on the keyboard.  This functionality is implemented using:  1. Hidden Button  A Bootstrap modal trigger button is added but kept invisible using CSS. It is only used internally to open the modal.  2. Keyboard Detection (JavaScript)  A JavaScript key listener tracks every key the user types. When the user types the entire sequence "mohit", the script matches it and immediately triggers the hidden button to open the modal.  3. Bootstrap Modal  A standard Bootstrap modal pops up, containing form fields (like an input box for adding new data).
